1	\chapter{Sheaf condition along the structure-sheaf forget composite}
2	\label{chap:Cohomology_SheafCompose}
3	
4	This chapter records the first step of Phase A in \texttt{STRATEGY.md}: equipping the abstract Mathlib sheaf-cohomology pipeline with the link it needs to compute $H^1(C, \mathcal O_C)$ as an abelian group. It is the smallest unblocking unit of progress toward Definition~\ref{def:genus} (the genus of a smooth proper curve).
5	
6	The chapter introduces no protected declarations: every definition and lemma here is auxiliary, supporting the construction of $H^1(C, \mathcal O_C)$ in subsequent Phase A iterations.
7	
8	\section{Statement}
9	
10	Mathlib has the abstract Grothendieck-topology sheaf-cohomology API
11	\lstinline{CategoryTheory.Sheaf.H : Sheaf J AddCommGrpCat → ℕ → Type w'}, but the structure sheaf $\mathcal O_C$ of a scheme is delivered by Mathlib in the shape \lstinline{TopCat.Sheaf CommRingCat C} (i.e.\ $\mathrm{CommRing}$-valued, not $\mathrm{Ab}$-valued). To plug $\mathcal O_C$ into the cohomology API we must first transport the sheaf condition along the forgetful composite $\mathrm{CommRing} \to \mathrm{Ring} \to \mathrm{Ab}$. The \lstinline{HasSheafCompose} typeclass packages exactly this transport.
12	
13	\begin{theorem}[Sheaf condition transports along the structure-sheaf forget composite]
14	  \label{thm:HasSheafCompose_forget}
15	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Cohomology.instHasSheafCompose_forget_CommRing_AddCommGrp}
16	  \leanok
17	  Let $X$ be a topological space. Then the Grothendieck topology of opens of $X$ has
18	  \[
19	    \mathtt{HasSheafCompose}\bigl(
20	      \mathrm{forget}_2\, \mathrm{CommRingCat}\, \mathrm{RingCat} \;\circ\;
21	      \mathrm{forget}_2\, \mathrm{RingCat}\, \mathrm{AddCommGrpCat}
22	    \bigr).
23	  \]
24	\end{theorem}
25	
26	In Lean:
27	\begin{lstlisting}
28	instance (X : TopCat) :
29	    (TopologicalSpace.Opens.grothendieckTopology X).HasSheafCompose
30	      (CategoryTheory.forget₂ CommRingCat RingCat ⋙
31	       CategoryTheory.forget₂ RingCat AddCommGrpCat)
32	\end{lstlisting}
33	
34	\section{Proof sketch}
35	
36	\begin{proof}
37	  \leanok
38	  Both $\mathrm{forget}_2 \mathrm{CommRingCat}\, \mathrm{RingCat}$ and $\mathrm{forget}_2 \mathrm{RingCat}\, \mathrm{AddCommGrpCat}$ are algebraic structure-forgetful functors and hence \emph{create} (in particular preserve) all small limits. The sheaf condition for the topology of opens is expressed as preservation of certain limits of the form \lstinline{multiequalizer (Cover.index ...)} (see \lstinline{Presheaf.IsSheaf.isSheaf_iff_isSheaf_of_type} and the multispan-limit reformulation \lstinline{IsSheaf.isLimit_multifork}). Composing two limit-preserving functors gives a limit-preserving functor, so the post-composition with the forget composite preserves the sheaf condition. The \lstinline{HasSheafCompose} typeclass is exactly the resulting "sheaf-of-rings becomes sheaf-of-abelian-groups" lemma.
39	\end{proof}
40	
41	\section{Use in the project}
42	
43	Theorem~\ref{thm:HasSheafCompose_forget} is the gateway to:
44	
45	\begin{itemize}
46	  \item the construction of $\mathcal O_C$ as a sheaf of abelian groups on $C$, by post-composing $\mathcal O_C : \mathrm{Opens}(C)^{\mathrm{op}} \to \mathrm{CommRingCat}$ with the forget composite — the resulting object lives in $\mathrm{Sheaf}(\mathrm{Opens.gT}\, C, \mathrm{AddCommGrpCat})$ thanks to the typeclass above;
47	  \item plugging that sheaf into \lstinline{CategoryTheory.Sheaf.H} once \lstinline{HasSheafify (Opens.gT C) AddCommGrpCat} and \lstinline{HasExt} are available (Phase A steps 2--3);
48	  \item endowing the resulting $H^1$ with a $k$-vector-space structure via the $k$-algebra structure on $\Gamma(C, \mathcal O_C)$ (Phase A step 4);
49	  \item finite-dimensionality via Serre's theorem on coherent cohomology of proper $k$-schemes (Phase A step 5);
50	  \item Definition~\ref{def:genus} ($g(C) = \dim_k H^1(C, \mathcal O_C)$) which then becomes formalisable.
51	\end{itemize}
52	
53	The chain is: \texttt{HasSheafCompose} (this chapter) $\to$ \texttt{HasSheafify} $\to$ \texttt{HasExt} $\to$ $\mathrm{Module}\, k$-on-$H^1$ $\to$ Serre finiteness $\to$ \lstinline{genus}.
54	
55	\section{Mathlib gap}
56	
57	Mathlib \texttt{b80f227} has all the constituent pieces:
58	\begin{itemize}
59	  \item \lstinline{CategoryTheory.GrothendieckTopology.HasSheafCompose} — the typeclass to populate.
60	  \item \lstinline{CategoryTheory.HasForget₂} for $\mathrm{CommRingCat} \to \mathrm{RingCat}$ (\lstinline{CommRingCat.hasForgetToRingCat}) and $\mathrm{RingCat} \to \mathrm{AddCommGrpCat}$ (\lstinline{RingCat.hasForgetToAddCommGrp}).
61	  \item Limit-preservation lemmas for algebraic forgetful functors and the sheaf-condition reformulations.
62	\end{itemize}
63	
64	What is missing and supplied by this chapter: the assembled \texttt{HasSheafCompose} instance for the specific composite $\mathrm{CommRingCat} \to \mathrm{AddCommGrpCat}$ on the Grothendieck topology of opens of an arbitrary topological space.
65	
