1	\chapter{Genus of a smooth proper curve}
2	\label{chap:Genus}
3	
4	Throughout this chapter, $k$ denotes a field and $C$ a smooth proper geometrically irreducible scheme over $k$ of relative dimension $1$ — that is, $C \to \Spec k$ carries the typeclasses
5	\lstinline{[SmoothOfRelativeDimension 1 C.hom] [IsProper C.hom] [GeometricallyIrreducible C.hom]}.
6	We call such a $C$ a \emph{smooth proper curve over $k$}.
7	
8	\section{Definition}
9	
10	\begin{definition}[Genus of a smooth proper curve]
11	  \label{def:genus}
12	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.genus}
13	  \leanok
14	  The \emph{genus} of a smooth proper curve $C$ over $k$ is the natural number
15	  \[
16	    g(C) \;=\; \dim_k H^1(C,\, \mathcal O_C),
17	  \]
18	  the $k$-dimension of the first sheaf-cohomology group of the structure sheaf of $C$.
19	\end{definition}
20	
21	Equivalent reformulations available once Riemann–Roch and Serre duality are formalised:
22	\begin{itemize}
23	  \item $g(C) = \dim_k H^0(C,\, \Omega^1_{C/k})$ (Serre duality).
24	  \item $g(C) = 1 - \chi(\mathcal O_C)$, where $\chi$ is the Euler characteristic.
25	  \item For a smooth projective curve over $\mathbb C$, $g(C)$ equals the topological genus of $C(\mathbb C)$.
26	\end{itemize}
27	Each of these requires Mathlib infrastructure that is currently absent (see Section \ref{sec:Genus_status}).
28	
29	\section{Mathlib gap}
30	\label{sec:Genus_status}
31	
32	The honest definition $\dim_k H^1(C, \mathcal O_C)$ requires:
33	
34	\begin{itemize}
35	  \item \textbf{Sheaf cohomology of quasi-coherent sheaves on schemes.} Mathlib has the abstract right-derived-functor machinery (\lstinline{CategoryTheory.Functor.RightDerived}) but no instantiation to $\Gamma(X, -) \colon \mathrm{QCoh}(X) \to \mathrm{Mod}_{\mathcal O_X(X)}$. Only étale/$\ell$-adic cohomology exists (\lstinline{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.EllAdicCohomology}), which is not what we need.
36	  \item \textbf{Finite-dimensionality of $H^i(C, \mathcal F)$ for coherent $\mathcal F$ on a proper scheme over a field} (Serre's theorem). Absent.
37	\end{itemize}
38	
39	\subsection{Discovery objective for this iteration}
40	
41	The prover should:
42	\begin{enumerate}
43	  \item Search Mathlib (\texttt{lean\_local\_search}, \texttt{lean\_leansearch}, \texttt{lean\_loogle}) for any existing API that computes $H^1(C, \mathcal O_C)$ as a $k$-vector space, including via Čech cohomology, hypercoverings, or derived functors.
44	  \item Document the precise API gap in \lstinline{task_results/Genus.md}: which type or function would have to exist for the definition to typecheck, and what the closest existing Mathlib declaration is.
45	  \item \textbf{Do not} introduce a placeholder definition (such as \lstinline{genus := 0} or an opaque \lstinline{Classical.choice}); leave the \lstinline{sorry} in place rather than weakening the mathematical content.
46	  \item If — and only if — the cohomology API is found in Mathlib, fill the \lstinline{sorry} with the honest definition.
47	\end{enumerate}
48	
49	The phase-A roadmap in \texttt{STRATEGY.md} tracks how the missing cohomology API is to be built across subsequent iterations.
